ll trades exploiting perceived color differences; badger makes more aggressive attempts to acquire RED and BLUE and shed PURPLE or possibly GREEN; cat tries to upgrade from RED into BLUE or PURPLE when offered good terms, and declines trades that give away these higher-valued colors too cheaply. Some mutually beneficial trades occur, but many proposals are rejected as players test the market and protect against exchanging away high-value chips for low-value ones under their own valuations.",
