rpart is more responsive to particular chip types. Because responses are simultaneous and the realized partner is randomized when multiple accept, proposers must consider that overly attractive offers can unintentionally benefit their less-preferred partner. A common pattern is therefore mildly favorable but not extreme offers, designed to induce exactly one acceptance from the targeted counterpart or to be satisfactory regardless of which responder gets selected. This forecast selects one internally consistent path where modest, mutually beneficial trades occur in early turns, and later turns refine positions without anyone fully arbitraging all private value differences within just three rounds.",
